No, this is not a fondue, at least not yet. Filled with a yellowish, curdled liquid, this large wooden vat contains a slowly-setting cheese. When ready, it shall become a cheese-lover's dream, with enough cheese to create the largest of fondues, large enough to dunk even a whole kobold into. Though why anyone should wish to make Kobold Fondue is quite perplexing...unless of course it was a particularly annoying singing kobold.

This massive stone statue looms high above you. Long ago shaped by dwarven hands into the likeness of a proud warrior, the figure stands as unyielding and resolute as the stone from which it was carved.
This old statue masterfully depicts the likeness of a dwarven warrior in a battle pose. A double-handed axe is readied against any enemies and a look of defiance shows in the face.
The head of this bear has been mounted on a wooden plaque as a trophy.
